<item>
            <title>[JDK-8314759] VirtualThread.parkNanos timeout adjustment when pinned should be replaced</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8314759</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>If yielding fails due to the pinning then VirtualThread.parkNanos parks on the carrier thread with the remaining time. The calculation of the remaining time should be changed to:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
long remainingNanos = nanos - (System.nanoTime() - startTime);&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The current code isn&amp;#39;t correct for cases where System.nanoTimes return a negative value or when parking for durations close to Long.MAX_VALUE (292 years).</description>
